With the assumption that _all_ functions in the call are of the same type, then it can be done with a simple generic type on the method:

    public static &lt;T&gt; T chain(
            T val,
            Function&lt;T, T&gt;... functions
    ) {
        if (functions.length == 0) return val;
        var nextInput = functions[0].apply(val);
        if (functions.length == 1) return nextInput;
        var tail = Arrays.copyOfRange(functions, 1, functions.length);
        return chain(nextInput, tail);
    }

There are other improvements that could be made (e.g. just using an index counter for the recursion to avoid array copies, or not being recursive). Be extra careful of boundary conditions, e.g. passing an empty call.

Using this, you may use any type for the input, and the functions will require operating on the same input and output types.

