In that code we use try-with-resources syntax to automatically shutdown the executor service after all submitted tasks are done. If you want to stop the executor service from accepting more tasks, call `shutdown`. If you want to halt submitted tasks, call `shutdownNow` and write your task classes to be aware of possible interruption. 


